Initial gravitational potential energy,
$$
E_i=-\frac{G M m}{2 R}
$$
Final gravitational potential energy,
$$
\begin{aligned}
E_f &=-\frac{G M m / 2}{2\left(\frac{R}{2}\right)}-\frac{G M m / 2}{2\left(\frac{3 R}{2}\right)} \\
&=-\frac{G M m}{2 R}-\frac{G M m}{6 R} \\
&=-\frac{4 G M m}{6 R}=-\frac{2 G M m}{3 R}
\end{aligned}
$$
$\therefore$ Difference between initial and final energy,
$$
E_f-E_i=\frac{G M m}{R}\left(-\frac{2}{3}+\frac{1}{2}\right)=-\frac{G M m}{6 R}
$$

